		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Mar 7th 10:33 AM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=98397752991792&num=1&page=&post=1&replyto=98397919891786"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=98397919891786></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=2048"><span id=Sage>SouldragoonFlamingheart</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>144 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Well, welcome to our esteemed ranks.&nbsp;&nbsp;=)  I've posted several times about the worth of skill points.  Some people have caught on, but there are still some people who doubt my advice. =P  Skill points are useless when used to up trade skills or combat skills, unless it requires 1 point to be invested to learn it and begin using it (like bash, dodge, evade, parry, double attack, riposte).  Once you are able to use a skill, don't waste your skill points on them anymore, because they go up for free through use.  Also, trade skills can only have skill points invested up to 20, but those first 20 are the easiest, cheapist, and quickest skill points to make when beginning a new trade.  Yes, taunt is extremely important for us, cuz we are one of those tank classes that can take a few blows for the group.  Just use it often if you have the most ac out of the group.  If someone has higher ac, it's usually wiser to let them taunt and save the healer's mana, unless they are losin alot of hp, then taunt off of em.<br><br>I know that it may seem a bother to start a weapon skill from 0, but really, do you notice THAT much difference from 0 and 20?  Don't waste them there either, it goes up fast through use, cuz yer ALWAYS swingin yer weapon.  =P  Once you get up to about lvl 30 or so, you will have enough skill points to invest into a single language that you don't know, and get it all the way up to the same level as common.  Languages are a tradeable with others, and many quests are still unknown because certain npc's respond to specific dialects (that came out from a producers letter a long long time ago), but nobody has really been able to figure them out cuz everyone is too used to just using common all the time.  =)  I have my elder dragon all the way up, and I'm waiting to be able to enter veeshan's stomping grounds and snoop around the npcs...<br><br>As for your original thought, yes, caster classes are difficult to level up at the start, but clerics in particular have no problems finding groups in the 30+ game.  Clerics and enchanters are valuable in all the 30+ zones.  It doesn't matter what class you play (except for rogues, heh, they just plain suck) just as long as you have fun playing it.  Just keep at it, make friends, and enjoy your time in eq while it lasts.  And if you were on the fennin server, I would have been happy to have invited you.  =)<br><br>Souldragoon Flamingheart<br>44th circle Paladin of Virtue<br>Fennin Ro</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><i>Follow virtue, and the virtuous will follow you.</i></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=98397752991792&num=1&page=&post=1&mid=98397752991792><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 class=mform><tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>1 Post [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class6">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
